	- Manual test against PRD user stories 21-28 (Wi-Fi network switching)
	- Manual test against PRD user stories 4, 5, 13-15 (Ethernet, multiple connections)
	- Regression test: PRD user stories 1-2, 8-9 (Phase 1 features still work)
	Discoveries:
		- CWSecurity in Swift 6: no .wep case (use .dynamicWEP), case names are lowercase (.dynamicWEP not .DynamicWEP)
		- CWConfiguration.networkProfiles returns non-optional NSOrderedSet — cast elements to CWNetworkProfile
		- CWInterface.associate(to:password:) accepts nil password for open/known networks
		- scanForNetworks(withName: nil) blocks for 1-3 seconds — always call off main thread
		- Advanced network detail toggles gated behind LicenseManager.isPaid (stub returns false); basic details (SSID, signal) always free
		- Menu bar icon changed from distinctive antenna to standard wifi/wifi.slash/cable.connector.horizontal to match connection state per PRD stories 4-5

